[Course_Description]
Awakening Compassion at Work considers the role of compassion in the workplace. It demonstrates the methods individuals and organizations can use to develop a culture of empathy and compassion, and shows how individuals and companies alike can benefit from such an approach. In this audio-only summary of this insightful book, you can learn how compassion can be a source of innovation for your organization. Discover techniques to increase compassion, curiosity, empathy, and perspective, and find out how to lead with compassion and translate that energy into action. Note: This audiobook summary was produced by Blinkist. We are pleased to host this content in our library.